debt and private equity investments. In addition to providing capital to portfolio companies, he was an integral part of the capital formation activities of the firm, including the placement of public and private debt and equity securities with major commercial lenders and institutional and public investors. He has served on numerous boards of portfolio companies and has been an advisor to several private companies.\r\n\r\nMr. Giffin began his career in public accounting with Arthur Andersen where he became a Tax Manager after initially serving on the audit staff. He was also a partner in a New Orleans-based regional accounting firm providing accounting and advisory services to public and private middle-market companies prior to joining the investment industry.\r\n\r\nMr. Giffin is a Certified Public Accountant and received a B.S. in Business Administration and Accounting from the University of Louisiana at Lafayette.'),(500,55,'_bio','field_6038030622bb8'),(501,55,'phone','985.7277228'),(502,55,'_phone','field_603804c322bba'),(503,55,'email','pgiffin@jeffcap.com'),(504,55,'_email','field_603804cf22bbb'),(505,56,'_us_in_content_ids',''),(506,56,'_us_grid_filter_atts',''),(507,56,'_edit_lock','1614898482:1'),(508,56,'_edit_last','1'),(509,56,'us_header_id','__defaults__'),(510,56,'us_header_sticky_override','0'),(511,56,'us_header_sticky',NULL),(512,56,'us_header_transparent_override','0'),(513,56,'us_header_transparent',NULL),(514,56,'us_header_shadow','0'),(515,56,'us_header_sticky_pos',''),(516,56,'us_content_id','__defaults__'),(517,56,'us_footer_id','__defaults__'),(518,56,'us_tile_bg_color',''),(519,56,'us_tile_text_color',''),(520,56,'us_tile_size','1x1'),(521,56,'us_tile_link','{\"url\":\"\",\"target\":\"\"}'),(522,56,'us_tile_additional_image',''),(523,56,'us_tile_icon',''),(524,56,'us_meta_title',''),(525,56,'us_meta_description',''),(526,56,'us_meta_robots',''),(527,56,'title','Partner'),(528,56,'_title','field_603804b222bb9'),(529,56,'bio','Mr. Cazayouxs career includes over thirteen years of mezzanine investment and commercial banking experience. Prior to joining Jefferson Capital in 2002, Mr. Cazayoux spent several years with First Bank and Trust, a New Orleans, Louisiana based commercial bank, where he managed a portfolio of mezzanine investments in small private companies made through a subsidiary of First Bank and Trust, as well as a portfolio of some of the largest commercial banking customers of First Bank.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining First Bank and Trust, Mr. Cazayoux spent several years with Bank One Louisiana, and its predecessor, First Commerce Corporation in a variety of roles, where among other things, he worked as an investment analyst with First Commerce Capital, Inc., a Small Business Investment Company, wholly-owned by First Commerce Corporation. Mr. Cazayoux began his career in the field of engineering at the Energy Division of the Louisiana Department of Natural Resources.\r\n\r\nMr. Cazayoux received a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering from Louisiana State University in 1991 and an MBA from the Goizueta Business School at Emory University in 1996.'),(530,56,'_bio','field_6038030622bb8'),(531,56,'phone','985.7277230'),(532,56,'_phone','field_603804c322bba'),(533,56,'email','fcazayoux@jeffcap.com'),(534,56,'_email','field_603804cf22bbb'),(535,57,'_us_in_content_ids',''),(536,57,'_us_grid_filter_atts',''),(537,57,'_edit_lock','1614898491:1'),(538,57,'_edit_last','1'),(539,57,'us_header_id','__defaults__'),(540,57,'us_header_sticky_override','0'),(541,57,'us_header_sticky',NULL),(542,57,'us_header_transparent_override','0'),(543,57,'us_header_transparent',NULL),(544,57,'us_header_shadow','0'),(545,57,'us_header_sticky_pos',''),(546,57,'us_content_id','__defaults__'),(547,57,'us_footer_id','__defaults__'),(548,57,'us_tile_bg_color',''),(549,57,'us_tile_text_color',''),(550,57,'us_tile_size','1x1'),(551,57,'us_tile_link','{\"url\":\"\",\"target\":\"\"}'),(552,57,'us_tile_additional_image',''),(553,57,'us_tile_icon',''),(554,57,'us_meta_title',''),(555,57,'us_meta_description',''),(556,57,'us_meta_robots',''),(557,57,'title','Partner'),(558,57,'_title','field_603804b222bb9'),(559,57,'bio','Les Alexander is an experienced private equity investor, mezzanine lender, corporate executive, and investment banker. He has significant knowledge of private equity and mezzanine investing having worked at Advantage Capital Partners and MSB Fairway Capital Partners prior to joining Jefferson Capital. Mr. Alexander served on the board of directors of several portfolio companies where he was actively involved in strategic planning and corporate governance.\r\n\r\nMr. Alexander served as president of Ferrara Fire Apparatus, Inc., a leading fire truck and emergency vehicle manufacturer. At Ferrara, he was responsible for managing a workforce of 450 employees producing over 300 vehicles annually for its domestic and international customers.\r\n\r\nAs an investment banker for 15 years with Howard Weil, Southcoast Capital, J.C. Bradford & Co., and LeCorgne Loewenbaum, Mr. Alexander completed over 50 public offerings of debt and equity securities, private placements, and merger and acquisition transactions totaling more than $7 billion for public and private companies in a variety of industries.\r\n\r\nMr. Alexander is an adjunct professor at Tulane University and Loyola University where he teaches graduate and undergraduate classes in investment banking, private equity & venture capital, advanced financial management, and entrepreneurship. He is also a board member and chairman of the audit committee for Benjamin Franklin High School, a charter school in New Orleans. Mr. Alexander is the former Chairman of Finance of the Association for Corporate Growth (ACG) and served on the global Board of Directors. He is a founder of the Louisiana chapter of ACG and was a recipient of the ACG global Meritorious Service Award and the Louisiana chapters Outstanding Service Award.\r\n\r\nMr. Alexander received his bachelor of science in Commerce from the University of Virginia in 1989 and his MBA from the University of North Carolina in 1993.'),(560,57,'_bio','field_6038030622bb8'),(561,57,'phone','985.3770003'),(562,57,'_phone','field_603804c322bba'),(563,57,'email','lalexander@jeffcap.com'),(564,57,'_email','field_603804cf22bbb'),(565,58,'_us_in_content_ids',''),(566,58,'_us_grid_filter_atts',''),(567,58,'_edit_lock','1614898500:1'),(568,58,'_edit_last','1'),(569,58,'us_header_id','__defaults__'),(570,58,'us_header_sticky_override','0'),(571,58,'us_header_sticky',NULL),(572,58,'us_header_transparent_override','0'),(573,58,'us_header_transparent',NULL),(574,58,'us_header_shadow','0'),(575,58,'us_header_sticky_pos',''),(576,58,'us_content_id','__defaults__'),(577,58,'us_footer_id','__defaults__'),(578,58,'us_tile_bg_color',''),(579,58,'us_tile_text_color',''),(580,58,'us_tile_size','1x1'),(581,58,'us_tile_link','{\"url\":\"\",\"target\":\"\"}'),(582,58,'us_tile_additional_image',''),(583,58,'us_tile_icon',''),(584,58,'us_meta_title',''),(585,58,'us_meta_description',''),(586,58,'us_meta_robots',''),(587,58,'title','Investment Manager'),(588,58,'_title','field_603804b222bb9'),(589,58,'bio','Mr. Truhes career includes over 10 years of investing experience. Prior to joining Jefferson Capital in 2013, Mr. Truhe was a Portfolio Manager with Whitney Bank in New Orleans, Louisiana, where he oversaw the companys Trust accounts and served as the Energy sector analyst for the Hancock Horizon Funds. Prior to Whitney, Mr. Truhe was an analyst and member of the investment committee at HFR Asset Management, a multi-billion dollar hedge fund platform in Chicago, Illinois. There, Mr. Truhe reviewed and maintained investment discretion over the firms Event-Driven and Asia-focused hedge fund allocations. He was also responsible for the expansion of the firms Asia-focused fund offerings.\r\n\r\nMr. Truhe holds a BA in Economics from Yale University, where he was a member of the Mens Ba